Verant should alter the respawn times so that they rotate around the 24 hour clock.  As an example, mob &quot;A&quot; respawns in 23 hours.  Guild &quot;B&quot; kills the mob and can time the respawn to be there to kill that mob again, then again, and again.  Alter the respawn time so that the mobs rotates 8 to 10 hours on the 24 hour clock.  This means that a mob would say spawn on one day at say 1500 in the afternoon, +/- a couple.  The next day, he respawns at about say midnight, +/-, 8 to 10 hours later.  This would allow the mob to be up and available for those players who are in radically different time zones like Europe or Asia to get a chance at taking down that mob.<br>
